1
00:00:06,320 --> 00:00:07,320
Zhou Yi, come check out Lin You's comic!

2
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:10,320
Lin You, you really spiced this up, didn't you?

3
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:13,320
The story

4
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:15,320
is adapted from my experiences at Lucky Realty.

5
00:01:10,320 --> 00:01:11,280
Stigmatized property.

6
00:01:12,440 --> 00:01:13,520
That refers to homes

7
00:01:14,280 --> 00:01:16,760
where unnatural deaths have occurred.

8
00:01:18,600 --> 00:01:19,400
Usually,

9
00:01:20,160 --> 00:01:22,680
people think living there brings bad luck.

10
00:01:24,240 --> 00:01:25,560
But Lucky Realty

11
00:01:26,640 --> 00:01:28,600
specializes in renting and selling these.

12
00:01:30,320 --> 00:01:32,440
They send employees to do trial stays.

13
00:01:34,640 --> 00:01:35,160
This

14
00:01:35,960 --> 00:01:37,720
is my first day on the job.

15
00:01:39,120 --> 00:01:39,920
So...

16
00:01:40,680 --> 00:01:42,200
have you stayed in a stigmatized property?

17
00:01:44,040 --> 00:01:46,080
Stay back! Stay back!

18
00:01:47,800 --> 00:01:48,600
It's a hallucination.

19
00:01:49,040 --> 00:01:50,000
It has to be a hallucination.

20
00:01:59,720 --> 00:02:00,520
It's a dream.

21
00:02:01,160 --> 00:02:02,240
It has to be a dream.

22
00:02:03,120 --> 00:02:04,840
This is just an ordinary house.

23
00:02:06,520 --> 00:02:07,320
Calm down.

24
00:02:08,320 --> 00:02:09,479
Calm down, Lin You.

25
00:02:10,680 --> 00:02:12,520
Everything just now was a hallucination.

26
00:02:13,160 --> 00:02:14,040
It's fine.

27
00:02:15,040 --> 00:02:15,960
It's fine.

28
00:02:18,160 --> 00:02:20,120
Kill me! Kill me!

29
00:02:20,680 --> 00:02:22,360
Kill me!

30
00:02:26,080 --> 00:02:27,000
Isn't this a dream?

31
00:02:27,280 --> 00:02:28,480
Something's really wrong with this house.

32
00:02:30,160 --> 00:02:30,840
No.

33
00:02:31,240 --> 00:02:32,920
I must just be too nervous.

34
00:02:35,080 --> 00:02:37,000
Kill me! Kill me!

35
00:02:37,560 --> 00:02:39,240
Kill me!

36
00:02:42,880 --> 00:02:44,640
This house is seriously creepy.

37
00:02:45,440 --> 00:02:47,360
I heard around two in the morning,

38
00:02:47,680 --> 00:02:49,000
there's always knocking at the door,

39
00:02:49,440 --> 00:02:50,520
but no one's ever there.

40
00:02:51,320 --> 00:02:52,360
You'd better be careful.

41
00:02:52,720 --> 00:02:55,000
You told our boss you'd work off the debt.

42
00:02:55,280 --> 00:02:57,400
Do the trial stay to get your stuff back.

43
00:02:58,240 --> 00:03:00,320
I must be crazy to listen to that woman.

44
00:03:06,480 --> 00:03:07,280
Who is it?

45
00:03:17,440 --> 00:03:18,240
Oh, and one more thing.

46
00:03:18,680 --> 00:03:20,040
The magic circle I taught you,

47
00:03:20,240 --> 00:03:21,280
you have to set it up properly.

48
00:03:24,600 --> 00:03:25,560
It's to save your life.

49
00:03:26,600 --> 00:03:28,360
Especially after midnight.

50
00:03:28,920 --> 00:03:30,280
If there really is something there,

51
00:03:30,920 --> 00:03:32,920
the magic circle's talisman and salt rings

52
00:03:33,240 --> 00:03:34,280
will react to it.

53
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:05,880
Pe-Pe-Person! Who are you?

54
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:06,800
Person.

55
00:04:08,520 --> 00:04:09,320
Person.

56
00:04:11,280 --> 00:04:12,240
You're trying to kill me!

57
00:04:18,519 --> 00:04:19,760
Didn't Liu Liu tell you?

58
00:04:20,200 --> 00:04:21,560
She sent me to keep watch with you.

59
00:04:35,040 --> 00:04:36,040
You're with Lucky Realty too?

60
00:04:38,160 --> 00:04:39,040
Never seen you before.

61
00:04:39,720 --> 00:04:40,880
I'm sort of...

62
00:04:41,040 --> 00:04:42,200
a part-time consultant, I guess.

63
00:04:42,680 --> 00:04:45,040
I help out in emergencies.

64
00:04:47,960 --> 00:04:49,240
Is anyone else from Lucky coming?

65
00:04:50,280 --> 00:04:51,440
Just me. No one else.

66
00:04:52,080 --> 00:04:52,880
Don't open the door!

67
00:04:53,520 --> 00:04:54,320
Who's there?

68
00:04:56,560 --> 00:04:57,800
Damn, nobody's here.

69
00:04:59,400 --> 00:05:00,600
That's pretty weird.

70
00:05:13,200 --> 00:05:14,200
What's wrong with you?

71
00:05:15,200 --> 00:05:16,000
Liu Liu said

72
00:05:16,120 --> 00:05:18,080
this place keeps hearing knocks at midnight.

73
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:19,680
The tenant suspects it's haunted.

74
00:05:19,840 --> 00:05:20,880
They hired us to investigate.

75
00:05:27,200 --> 00:05:27,760
Fine.

76
00:05:28,040 --> 00:05:29,880
Won't knock if I leave the door open, huh?

77
00:05:50,440 --> 00:05:51,520
Here, hold this for me.

78
00:05:59,960 --> 00:06:00,960
Is this really that boring?

79
00:06:03,080 --> 00:06:03,720
Who?

80
00:06:06,720 --> 00:06:07,520
Zhou Yi!

81
00:06:09,720 --> 00:06:10,520
Zhou Yi!

82
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:11,600
Zhou Yi!

83
00:06:22,920 --> 00:06:23,720
Damn.

84
00:06:25,400 --> 00:06:26,800
How can he run so fast?

85
00:06:27,520 --> 00:06:28,520
He's The Flash!

86
00:06:33,960 --> 00:06:34,680
Open the door!

87
00:06:34,920 --> 00:06:36,280
You people have no shame!

88
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:37,920
Ma'am, ma'am.

89
00:06:39,280 --> 00:06:41,320
We haven't confirmed it's this family.

90
00:06:41,560 --> 00:06:43,640
Wait till we get back and look into it.

91
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:45,240
Look into what?

92
00:06:45,320 --> 00:06:46,400
It's definitely them.

93
00:06:46,680 --> 00:06:48,680
They have hearts as black as coal.

94
00:06:48,680 --> 00:06:50,160
The whole family's rotten.

95
00:06:50,920 --> 00:06:51,840
Yes, ma'am.

96
00:06:52,440 --> 00:06:54,040
I'm guessing no one's home.

97
00:06:58,000 --> 00:06:58,800
Making all this fuss

98
00:06:59,040 --> 00:06:59,880
isn't going to help.

99
00:07:00,400 --> 00:07:01,760
Then what do you want me to do?

100
00:07:01,840 --> 00:07:03,320
My perfectly good house...

101
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:05,120
I just want to earn my kid's tuition.

102
00:07:05,720 --> 00:07:07,840
They pull this ghost-knocking crap daily.

103
00:07:07,920 --> 00:07:09,840
They've scared off three sets of tenants!

104
00:07:09,840 --> 00:07:11,440
Do you know how much I've lost?

105
00:07:13,560 --> 00:07:14,240
Yeah.

106
00:07:14,680 --> 00:07:15,400
Ma'am.

107
00:07:15,400 --> 00:07:16,440
Let me just ask,

108
00:07:17,400 --> 00:07:18,600
do you and this family

109
00:07:19,360 --> 00:07:20,960
have some kind of bad blood?

110
00:07:21,480 --> 00:07:22,440
What bad blood?

111
00:07:22,920 --> 00:07:24,200
They're just shameless,

112
00:07:24,360 --> 00:07:25,440
stirring up trouble for no reason.

113
00:07:29,160 --> 00:07:30,320
Move, get out of the way!

114
00:07:30,760 --> 00:07:32,480
What are you all doing at my house?

115
00:07:32,840 --> 00:07:33,640
Who are you? Sir, sir, sir!

116
00:07:33,640 --> 00:07:34,720
We're from upstairs.

117
00:07:34,720 --> 00:07:36,560
We just came to ask a few questions.

118
00:07:36,560 --> 00:07:37,960
Upstairs my foot!

119
00:07:38,400 --> 00:07:40,000
Your family are murderers!

120
00:07:40,160 --> 00:07:41,640
Your whole family are murderers!

121
00:07:43,440 --> 00:07:44,240
Sweetie.

122
00:07:49,280 --> 00:07:50,120
Sweetie.

123
00:07:51,640 --> 00:07:52,440
Sweetie.

124
00:07:53,360 --> 00:07:54,600
You're back.

125
00:07:55,840 --> 00:07:56,560
Dear, dear!

126
00:07:56,640 --> 00:07:57,680
What are you doing out here?

127
00:07:57,680 --> 00:07:58,480
Our daughter.

128
00:07:59,040 --> 00:08:00,040
Our daughter's back!

129
00:08:00,040 --> 00:08:00,880
Go, go, go!

130
00:08:00,880 --> 00:08:01,600
Get out, get out!

131
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:06,720
Your family are the murderers!

132
00:08:06,840 --> 00:08:08,040
Rotten to the core!

133
00:08:08,200 --> 00:08:09,520
You deserve every bit of karma!

134
00:08:10,760 --> 00:08:11,400
It's okay, ma'am.

135
00:08:11,400 --> 00:08:12,440
Let's go back and look into it more.

136
00:08:12,440 --> 00:08:14,040
We don't even know what's going on yet.

137
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:14,880
Forget it. It's fine, ma'am.

138
00:08:14,880 --> 00:08:15,800
Let's check again.

139
00:08:16,240 --> 00:08:17,480
Slow down, watch the step.

140
00:08:18,040 --> 00:08:19,360
It's okay, ma'am. Calm down.

141
00:08:31,840 --> 00:08:32,840
What are you doing here?

142
00:08:33,880 --> 00:08:35,120
What a coincidence, huh?

143
00:08:41,240 --> 00:08:42,240
Have some water, ma'am.

144
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:44,560
Where's your boss?

145
00:08:44,840 --> 00:08:45,880
Get your boss out here.

146
00:08:47,120 --> 00:08:48,360
The boss is out on business.

147
00:08:49,280 --> 00:08:50,280
You can talk to me.

148
00:08:51,160 --> 00:08:52,120
Talk to you?

149
00:08:52,600 --> 00:08:54,360
Unit 701 is pulling ghost tricks.

150
00:08:54,560 --> 00:08:55,760
I went to confront them.

151
00:08:57,040 --> 00:08:58,600
And you won't even back me up.

152
00:08:58,680 --> 00:08:59,480
What now?

153
00:08:59,880 --> 00:09:00,680
You tell me.

154
00:09:00,880 --> 00:09:01,680
What now?

155
00:09:07,560 --> 00:09:08,560
So it's confirmed to be a person?

156
00:09:12,360 --> 00:09:13,400
I already told you.

157
00:09:13,720 --> 00:09:14,920
It's Unit 701.

158
00:09:15,560 --> 00:09:16,320
A person.

159
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:17,800
It's a person.

160
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:20,320
Are you deaf or just clueless?

161
00:09:20,520 --> 00:09:21,360
All we found was

162
00:09:21,360 --> 00:09:22,880
the Bluetooth speaker faking the haunting.

163
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:24,960
But we don't know for sure it was them.

164
00:09:25,440 --> 00:09:26,920
Who else could it be?

165
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:29,000
That whole family is psycho.

166
00:09:31,680 --> 00:09:32,760
Psycho, huh?

167
00:09:36,160 --> 00:09:38,040
Psychos aren't easy to deal with.

168
00:09:43,480 --> 00:09:44,360
Where's the big oaf?

169
00:09:45,240 --> 00:09:47,120
You're in cahoots with upstairs.

170
00:09:47,840 --> 00:09:48,640
No, I'm not.

171
00:09:48,880 --> 00:09:49,760
I'm a real estate agent.

172
00:09:50,040 --> 00:09:52,200
Unit 801 wants to sell their place.

173
00:09:52,640 --> 00:09:55,320
But people keep reporting midnight knocks.

174
00:09:56,080 --> 00:09:57,120
Can't rent it out.

175
00:09:57,120 --> 00:09:58,080
Can't sell it either.

176
00:09:58,320 --> 00:09:59,880
So we came to check things out.

177
00:10:01,640 --> 00:10:02,840
A clear conscience

178
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:04,160
fears nothing.

179
00:10:04,680 --> 00:10:05,360
Was it...

180
00:10:06,720 --> 00:10:08,560
that Bluetooth speaker

181
00:10:08,960 --> 00:10:09,920
really placed by you?

182
00:10:11,120 --> 00:10:13,520
Tell that couple up in 801

183
00:10:19,360 --> 00:10:20,600
that she's the one who did it.

184
00:10:40,240 --> 00:10:41,040
Enough.

185
00:10:41,160 --> 00:10:42,680
You clearly can't solve this.

186
00:10:43,160 --> 00:10:44,840
Maybe you shouldn't take this deal.

187
00:10:44,840 --> 00:10:45,600
Don't say that, ma'am.

188
00:10:45,600 --> 00:10:47,360
My colleague is still talking to Unit 701.

189
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:48,880
Fine by me.

190
00:10:49,120 --> 00:10:50,000
The deposit isn't refundable.

191
00:10:50,360 --> 00:10:51,440
Just think it through.

192
00:10:55,840 --> 00:10:56,640
Li Zifan!

193
00:10:56,840 --> 00:10:57,560
Li Zifan!

194
00:10:57,560 --> 00:10:58,360
Coming!

195
00:10:59,280 --> 00:11:00,080
Let's go.

196
00:11:03,400 --> 00:11:04,360
You wanna die?

197
00:11:04,360 --> 00:11:05,480
You're the one who wants to die.

198
00:11:05,760 --> 00:11:06,440
Move.

199
00:11:09,160 --> 00:11:09,960
Hold on.

200
00:11:14,120 --> 00:11:16,440
The kid has to leave something behind.

201
00:11:17,280 --> 00:11:18,120
What did you take?

202
00:11:18,120 --> 00:11:19,120
What junk of theirs did you grab?

203
00:11:19,120 --> 00:11:19,880
Hurry up.

204
00:11:20,920 --> 00:11:21,720
Little one.

205
00:11:22,440 --> 00:11:23,520
The thing in your hand,

206
00:11:23,880 --> 00:11:25,200
it's my master's magical artifact.

207
00:11:25,920 --> 00:11:27,320
If you like it,

208
00:11:27,560 --> 00:11:28,760
you can just tell me.

209
00:11:29,880 --> 00:11:30,680
Stealing

210
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:32,240
isn't a good habit, you know.

211
00:11:32,240 --> 00:11:34,040
I picked it up off the floor.

212
00:11:34,160 --> 00:11:35,640
What junk did you pick up?

213
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:37,560
Come on, hand it over.

214
00:11:37,560 --> 00:11:38,320
I won't.

215
00:11:38,840 --> 00:11:39,840
You can't act like this, kid.

216
00:11:39,840 --> 00:11:40,480
Give it to me.

217
00:11:40,480 --> 00:11:41,160
Hand it over.

218
00:11:41,160 --> 00:11:42,080
What are you doing?

219
00:11:42,560 --> 00:11:44,080
Why's a grown-up fighting a kid?

220
00:11:45,560 --> 00:11:46,920
What's the big deal with this junk?

221
00:11:47,520 --> 00:11:48,600
Can't bear to give it to a client?

222
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:49,480
Just tell me the price.

223
00:11:49,480 --> 00:11:50,200
I'll buy it.

224
00:11:50,560 --> 00:11:51,320
No, wait.

225
00:11:51,320 --> 00:11:52,320
This belongs to our boss.

226
00:11:52,320 --> 00:11:53,160
I can't give it to you.

227
00:11:53,280 --> 00:11:54,240
Hand it over, you cheapskate.

228
00:11:54,240 --> 00:11:55,160
You ugly freak, give it here.

229
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:56,280
You all just work for my family.

230
00:11:56,280 --> 00:11:57,480
Everything here belongs to me.

231
00:11:57,520 --> 00:11:58,480
What are you doing?

232
00:11:58,840 --> 00:11:59,960
A grown-up acting like this with a kid?

233
00:11:59,960 --> 00:12:00,840
What's wrong with you?

234
00:12:01,680 --> 00:12:03,120
Do you know where you are?

235
00:12:04,560 --> 00:12:05,920
You just touch whatever you want?

236
00:12:07,320 --> 00:12:08,480
Watch your kid.

237
00:12:12,080 --> 00:12:12,760
Let's go.

238
00:12:13,400 --> 00:12:14,480
Always embarrassing me.

239
00:12:19,720 --> 00:12:20,720
That's so like you.

240
00:12:20,720 --> 00:12:21,440
Sister Yaoyao.

241
00:12:38,720 --> 00:12:40,360
What on earth did you take from someone?

242
00:12:40,360 --> 00:12:41,520
Grabbing every piece of junk you see.

243
00:12:41,760 --> 00:12:43,240
I just picked it up.

244
00:12:43,360 --> 00:12:44,520
Finders keepers.

245
00:12:44,720 --> 00:12:46,360
This holds so much resentful energy.

246
00:12:46,360 --> 00:12:47,440
Taking other people's stuff...

247
00:12:47,520 --> 00:12:48,960
and it actually latched onto you.

248
00:12:48,960 --> 00:12:50,000
Why can't I take it?

249
00:12:53,800 --> 00:12:54,960
You have to buy it for me!

250
00:12:55,040 --> 00:12:56,360
Then go tell your dad.

251
00:12:56,480 --> 00:12:57,120
What?

252
00:12:57,640 --> 00:12:58,400
Cheapskate.

253
00:12:58,600 --> 00:12:59,240
Let's get going.
